-- CICC Economist Ha Jiming to Join Goldman Sachs, Wall Street Journal Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-21T11:06:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-21/cicc-economist-ha-jiming-to-join-goldman-sachs-wall-street-journal-says.html

          
          
             China International Capital Corp.’s
chief economist Ha Jiming is leaving the Beijing-based
investment bank to join Goldman Sachs Group Inc.’s investment
banking division, the Wall Street Journal reported, citing
people familiar with the situation.  
 Ha will be a managing director at Goldman Sachs and is due
to start in October, the paper said.  
 Ha’s China mobile phone was switched off today.  
          
          


  


        